==English==
===Pronunciation===
*slĭp, /slɪp/, /<tt>slIp</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɪp|Rhymes: -ɪp]]

===Verb===
'''to slip''' ([[slips]], [[slipped]], [[slipping]])

====Intransitive====
# to lose one's traction on a slippery surface.
# to [[err]].

=====Translations=====
*Dutch: [[slippen]] (1), [[uitglijden]] (1), [[falen]]
*French: [[glisser]] (1)
*German: [[gleiten]] (1), [[fehlen]] (2)

====Transitive====
# to [[pass]] (a note, etc.)
#: ''The spy slipped his agent a coded message.''

=====Translations=====
*German: [[reichen]]

====Related terms====
*[[slippage]]
*[[slippery]]
*[[slipshod]]
*[[slip up]]

===Noun===
'''slip''' (plural: [[slips]])

# an act or instance of slipping.
# a women's undergarment worn under a skirt.
# a small piece of [[paper]].
# a [[berth]] for a boat or ship.
# a mistake ([[slip of the tongue]])
#(uncountable) in [[ceramics]], a thin, slippery mix of [[clay]] and [[water]]

